I"y<h2 id="declaration-follows-use">Declaration Follows Use</h2>

<p>In C, a pointer to int has type <code>int*</code>, but really, this isnâ€™t the right way of looking at it. For example, the following declaration:</p>

<pre><code class="language-C">int* x, y;
</code></pre>

<p>creates <code>x</code> of type <code>int*</code> and <code>y</code> of type <code>int</code>.</p>

